---
import ReportLayout from '@/components/ReportLayout.astro';
---

<ReportLayout title="Competitor Analysis Agent">

  <section class="agent-intro">
    <p class="agent-eyebrow">Agent Guide</p>
    <h1 class="agent-h1">Competitor Analysis</h1>
    <p class="agent-summary">
      The Competitor Analysis agent reviews a competitor's page side-by-side with the equivalent
      Myprotein page, and surfaces only genuine gaps — patterns the competitor does that Myprotein
      doesn't, or doesn't do as well. It's deliberately conservative: zero findings is a valid
      result, and a finding is only included if the agent can show both sides of the comparison with
      a screenshot. Use it when you're starting a redesign and want to know what the market is doing,
      or when a specific competitor is getting attention and you want to understand why.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Before you start ────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="guide-section">
    <h2 class="section-heading">Before you start</h2>
    <ul class="checklist">
      <li>The full URL of the competitor page you want analysed</li>
      <li>The full URL of the equivalent Myprotein page (e.g. their PDP vs our PDP for a comparable product)</li>
      <li>Both URLs should be publicly accessible — no login required</li>
      <li>Have a clear page type in mind (PDP, PLP, basket, checkout) — the agent compares like-for-like, not across different page types</li>
      <li>You're running Claude Code inside this repo so the agent can commit the output files</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <!-- ── How to trigger ──────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="guide-section">
    <h2 class="section-heading">How to trigger it</h2>
    <p class="guide-body">Use the slash command directly, or describe the comparison in plain English:</p>
    <div class="trigger-block">
      <code class="trigger-command">/competitor-analysis</code>
    </div>
    <div class="trigger-examples">
      <span class="trigger-chip">"compare Gymshark's PDP to ours"</span>
      <span class="trigger-chip">"what does Bulk do well on their basket?"</span>
      <span class="trigger-chip">"look at [competitor URL] and find opportunities"</span>
      <span class="trigger-chip">"anything worth stealing from this page?"</span>
    </div>
    <p class="guide-body guide-body--tip">Include both the competitor URL and the Myprotein URL in your message. If you only provide one URL, the agent will ask for the other before starting.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Step-by-step walkthrough ───────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="guide-section">
    <h2 class="section-heading">Step-by-step walkthrough</h2>
    <ol class="steps">
      <li class="step">
        <span class="step-number">1</span>
        <div class="step-body">
          <h3 class="step-title">URL validation and report slug</h3>
          <p class="step-desc">
            The agent confirms it has both URLs, identifies the page type (PDP, PLP, basket, etc.),
            and derives a report slug from the competitor brand name and page type, e.g.
            <code>pdp-competitor-analysis-2026-06-08</code>. It will confirm the slug with you if it's
            uncertain.
          </p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="step">
        <span class="step-number">2</span>
        <div class="step-body">
          <h3 class="step-title">Screenshot both pages</h3>
          <p class="step-desc">
            The agent opens both URLs in a headless browser at 1440px desktop width and scrolls
            through each page systematically, capturing screenshots of every major section.
            Screenshots of the competitor page are saved to
            <code>src/assets/reports/competitors/[slug]/</code>. Myprotein screenshots are captured
            inline for comparison but the agent uses existing Myprotein report assets where they're
            already available.
          </p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="step">
        <span class="step-number">3</span>
        <div class="step-body">
          <h3 class="step-title">Section-by-section comparison</h3>
          <p class="step-desc">
            The agent divides each page into sections (above the fold, product information, social
            proof, cross-sell, etc.) and compares each section across both pages. For every section
            it asks: does the competitor do something Myprotein doesn't? Is there a meaningful
            quality difference? It looks for patterns across UX, content strategy, trust signals,
            navigation, and conversion mechanics.
          </p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="step">
        <span class="step-number">4</span>
        <div class="step-body">
          <h3 class="step-title">Opportunities are filtered for genuine gaps</h3>
          <p class="step-desc">
            The agent applies a conservative filter: it only includes an opportunity if (a) the
            competitor demonstrably does it, (b) Myprotein demonstrably doesn't or does it worse,
            and (c) it would plausibly improve conversion, usability, or trust for Myprotein's
            audience. Parity items — where both pages perform similarly — are discarded.
          </p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="step">
        <span class="step-number">5</span>
        <div class="step-body">
          <h3 class="step-title">Report is written</h3>
          <p class="step-desc">
            The agent writes <code>src/pages/reports/competitors/[slug].astro</code> using the
            <code>ReportLayout</code> wrapper. Each opportunity card shows the competitor screenshot,
            the equivalent Myprotein state, a description of the gap, and a recommended action.
            If multiple competitors were reviewed in the same run, they're grouped by opportunity
            theme rather than brand.
          </p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="step">
        <span class="step-number">6</span>
        <div class="step-body">
          <h3 class="step-title">Agent hands back to you</h3>
          <p class="step-desc">
            The agent tells you how many opportunities it found and lists the files it created.
            If it found zero genuine opportunities, it explains which sections were reviewed and
            why nothing met the threshold — that's also useful information.
          </p>
        </div>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Committing the output ──────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="guide-section">
    <h2 class="section-heading">Committing the output</h2>

    <h3 class="sub-heading">Files created</h3>
    <ul class="file-list">
      <li><code>src/pages/reports/competitors/[slug].astro</code> — the analysis report page</li>
      <li><code>src/assets/reports/competitors/[slug]/*.png</code> — competitor screenshots</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="sub-heading">Git commands</h3>
    <pre class="code-block">git add src/pages/reports/competitors/[slug].astro src/assets/reports/competitors/[slug]/
git commit -m "Add competitor analysis: [Page Type] — [Brand(s)] ([date])"
git push</pre>

    <h3 class="sub-heading">Suggested commit message format</h3>
    <pre class="code-block">Add competitor analysis: PDP — Gymshark, Bulk, TPW (2026-06-08)</pre>

    <h3 class="sub-heading">Verifying the report is live</h3>
    <p class="guide-body">
      After pushing, visit <code>/reports/competitors/[slug]</code> on the deployed site once
      Vercel has redeployed (typically under 2 minutes). Check that all competitor screenshots
      load and the opportunity cards render correctly.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Example output ────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="guide-section">
    <h2 class="section-heading">Example output</h2>
    <p class="guide-body">
      The PDP competitor analysis from 8 June 2026 covers 6 brands — Gymshark, Bulk, TPW,
      Optimum Nutrition, MyVegan, and Naked Nutrition — and surfaces 14 opportunities across
      trust signals, content, and conversion mechanics:
    </p>
    <a href="/reports/competitors/pdp-competitor-analysis-2026-06-08" class="example-link">
      View: PDP Competitor Analysis (June 2026) →
    </a>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Tips and common issues ────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="guide-section">
    <h2 class="section-heading">Tips and common issues</h2>
    <ul class="tips-list">
      <li>
        <strong>Zero findings is a valid result.</strong>
        Don't interpret an empty report as a failure. It means the competitor doesn't do anything
        on that page that Myprotein doesn't already do. That's useful to know — it tells you the
        page is competitive and your design energy should go elsewhere.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Competitor page is behind a login or bot detection.</strong>
        Some competitor sites (especially checkout pages) block headless browsers. The agent will
        flag this in the report. For these pages, manually capture screenshots and describe the
        pattern to the agent — it can write a structured opportunity card from a description.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Only compare equivalent page types.</strong>
        A competitor's PDP compared to Myprotein's PLP won't produce useful output. Make sure both
        URLs are the same page type and, where possible, comparable product categories
        (e.g. protein powder vs protein powder, not protein vs clothing).
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Running multiple competitors in one session.</strong>
        You can pass multiple competitor URLs in one message — the agent will screenshot all of
        them and produce a single consolidated report grouped by opportunity theme. This is usually
        more useful than one report per brand.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Report includes something that Myprotein already does.</strong>
        Sometimes the agent misses a Myprotein feature on a specific page variant or test cell.
        If an opportunity is already addressed, add a note in the report file and commit — it
        keeps a historical record and you don't need to re-run the agent.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

</ReportLayout>

<style>
  .agent-intro { margin-bottom: 48px; }
  .agent-eyebrow {
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--color-primary);
    opacity: 0.5;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }
  .agent-h1 {
    font-size: clamp(26px, 4vw, 38px);
    font-weight: 800;
    color: var(--color-text-heading);
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    line-height: 1.15;
  }
  .agent-summary {
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text-body);
    max-width: 680px;
  }

  .guide-section { margin-bottom: 52px; }
  .section-heading {
    font-size: 20px;
    font-weight: 800;
    color: var(--color-text-heading);
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    padding-bottom: 10px;
    border-bottom: 2px solid rgba(0,57,66,0.08);
  }
  .sub-heading {
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-text-heading);
    margin: 20px 0 8px;
  }

  .guide-body {
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--color-text-body);
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }
  .guide-body--tip {
    background: var(--color-bg-muted);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-mint);
    padding: 10px 14px;
    border-radius: 0 6px 6px 0;
    margin-top: 12px;
  }

  .checklist {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 10px;
  }
  .checklist li {
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--color-text-body);
    padding-left: 22px;
    position: relative;
  }
  .checklist li::before {
    content: '→';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--color-primary);
    opacity: 0.4;
    font-size: 13px;
  }

  .trigger-block { margin-bottom: 16px; }
  .trigger-command {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 15px;
    font-family: 'SF Mono', 'Fira Code', monospace;
    background: var(--color-primary);
    color: var(--color-mint);
    padding: 8px 18px;
    border-radius: 8px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.01em;
  }
  .trigger-examples {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 8px;
    margin-bottom: 14px;
  }
  .trigger-chip {
    font-size: 13px;
    background: var(--color-bg-muted);
    border: var(--card-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-chip);
    padding: 5px 12px;
    color: var(--color-text-body);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  code {
    font-family: 'SF Mono', 'Fira Code', monospace;
    font-size: 12.5px;
    background: var(--color-bg-muted);
    color: var(--color-primary);
    padding: 2px 6px;
    border-radius: 4px;
  }

  .code-block {
    font-family: 'SF Mono', 'Fira Code', monospace;
    font-size: 13px;
    background: var(--color-bg-muted);
    color: var(--color-text-heading);
    padding: 16px 20px;
    border-radius: 8px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    overflow-x: auto;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    border: var(--card-border);
    white-space: pre;
  }

  .file-list {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 6px;
    margin-bottom: 4px;
  }
  .file-list li {
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--color-text-body);
    padding-left: 16px;
    position: relative;
  }
  .file-list li::before {
    content: '·';
    position: absolute;
    left: 4px;
    color: var(--color-primary);
    opacity: 0.4;
  }

  .steps { list-style: none; display: flex; flex-direction: column; }
  .step {
    display: flex;
    gap: 20px;
    align-items: flex-start;
    padding: 24px 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(0,57,66,0.08);
  }
  .step:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .step-number {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 34px;
    height: 34px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--color-primary);
    color: var(--color-mint);
    font-size: 13px;
    font-weight: 800;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    margin-top: 2px;
  }
  .step-title {
    font-size: 15px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-text-heading);
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }
  .step-desc {
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--color-text-body);
  }

  .example-link {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-primary);
    text-decoration: none;
    border: var(--card-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-card);
    padding: 14px 20px;
    background: var(--color-bg-card);
    transition: box-shadow 0.15s, transform 0.1s;
  }
  .example-link:hover {
    box-shadow: var(--card-shadow);
    transform: translateY(-1px);
  }

  .tips-list {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 16px;
  }
  .tips-list li {
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--color-text-body);
    background: var(--color-bg-card);
    border: var(--card-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-card);
    padding: 16px 18px;
  }
  .tips-list strong {
    display: block;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-text-heading);
    margin-bottom: 4px;
  }
</style>
